  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-30 19:25 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] F&G Correlation + Monday Trade Review\n\n**Task:** Correlate Fear & Greed with WR. Review first Monday with new filters.\n\n**Findings:**\n1. **F&G is useless as a signal right now** \u2014 ALL 161 trades happened during Extreme Fear (F&G 0-19). No data for other regimes. Can't correlate what doesn't vary.\n2. **Monday results: 3W/2L = 60% WR on 5 trades** (outcomes say 5, but logs show 6 executions). All YES bets at hour 11-12.\n3. **Duplicate trade bug is BACK** \u2014 two trades 7 seconds apart at 11:19 (same 5-min window), two more at 11:38-11:39. Per-window guard is broken.\n4. **Hour 19 completely blocked** \u2014 UP price at $0.540 > max_price $0.535. 46 price blocks today. Our second-best hour is being wasted.\n5. **V3.2 filter blocks NO trades at hour 11** \u2014 \"YES-only, NO=40% WR\". Forces us to wait for negative bias to buy YES.\n\n**My thinking:** Two competing problems:\n- max_price at $0.535 is too tight, blocking our best hours \u2192 should widen to $0.545\n- BUT higher price = higher break-even WR needed (54.5% at $0.545)\n- The duplicate trade bug is more urgent \u2014 it doubles our risk per window\n\n**Decision:** Fix duplicate bug first (P2 priority). Widen max_price to $0.545 with data backing needed. F&G not actionable until we trade in non-fear regime.\n\n**Next P4:** Build BTC volatility regime classifier (ATR-based). More useful differentiator than F&G.\n\n## 2026-03-30 20:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] Double-Trade Bug Persists: Added Timestamp Guard\n\n**Task:** Investigate why double-trade bug recurred at 20:17 despite `window_traded` fix.\n\n**Bug:** Two trades at 20:17:40 and 20:17:44 (3 seconds apart) in same 5-min window. Both YES @ $0.484, both WON (BTC 66574\u219266607). The `window_traded = True` fix from 11:38 was in place but didn't prevent it.\n\n**Root cause hypothesis:** The asyncio event loop processes WebSocket data between the `window_traded = True` assignment and the `await execute_trade()` call. During the first trade's API call, the loop picks up new WS data, re-enters the main loop, and fires a second trade before `window_traded` is checked. The 10s poll interval (`asyncio.sleep(10)`) should prevent re-entry, but WebSocket callbacks may trigger additional iterations.\n\n**Fix applied:** Added timestamp-based guard \u2014 minimum 30 seconds between trades:\n```python\nif hasattr(self, '_last_trade_ts') and (time.time() - self._last_trade_ts) < 30:\n    continue\n```\nThis is a belt-and-suspenders fix alongside `window_traded`. Even if the event loop somehow re-enters, the 30s cooldown prevents double-fire.\n\n**Bot restarted at 20:40.** Balance: $921.75 (PM payouts settling).\n\n**20h results:** 2 trades, 2 wins (bug dupes). Updated Day 1: **7 trades, 5W/2L = 71% WR**.\n\n## 2026-03-30 20:10 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] 20h = Weakest Active Hour: 60% WR, Zero Signals in Downtrends\n\n**Task:** Analyze 20h signal availability and historical performance.\n\n**Finding:**\n- **20h",
